snippet.title: YIIK IV Minimalist Trailer NO.1
snippet.description:
Music: 
Allanson
"Vella Wilde - DJ Set at the Literal Apocalypse"
Vocals by Mika Maruyama
YIIK I.V + Trinity (Coming Soon)

https://andrewallanson.bandcamp.com/track/vella-wilde-dj-set-at-the-literal-apocalypse?fbclid=IwAR0v6IF__DmI7E72owuhtytGCUGeWMW27Cyyl6zxkS_1fm2A-i_qOlvtSJA


Edited by SNESMAN99
Please like this video if I did a good job I might not have to get the job at the VHS store. I really don't want to. Mom says I owe $100 a month for my room now that I graduated and I just can't deal with that right now. I've got more important things to do. Seriously. Get off my case. Let me grow. let me breath. Let me be my own person. Don't shackle me with your corporate chains! Just as I refuse my Mother's demands that I became a wage cuck, I refuse traditional trailers! 

Ackk said I can do ONE trailer. Maybe two if this goes well otherwise they'll have to hire someone who studied film or has edited video before. 

I choose to get a liberal arts degree. To study the classics. To grappled with chaos and stare into the abyss. I fought with Jung and Freud, I trioka'd with Anna Karenina. What I lack in literal skill and talent I make up for in metaphorical merit. 

Mark my words.
